NAME
  parallel.pause
  
CALLS
  parallel.pause(uid)
  parallel.pause(uid, amount)
  
RETURNS
  boolean: true - if succeeded.
  boolean: false, string: errmsg - if failed.
  
DESCRIPTION
  Pauses thread for a given amount (default = 1) until it is unpaused.
  You can pause thread harder (amount = 2+) to make it not unpause after more than one parallel.unpause calls. 
  coroutine.Pause(thread) has the same effect as coroutine.Unpause(thread, -1). 
  
EXAMPLES
  parallel.pause(targetThreadUID)
  parallel.pause(targetThreadUID, 3)
  parallel.pause(targetThreadUID, -math.huge)
